"title": "8270: holiness, as set apart for God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8270",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Believers are holy, in that they are called to be set apart from the world as God's own people. Likewise certain days and articles are holy because they are set apart for God alone.</p>\n<h2>Believers are called to be a holy people, set apart for God</h2>\n<h3>The nation of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:6\">DEU 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:18-Deut26:19\">DEU 26:18–26:19</a></p>\n<h3>The priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:13\">1CH 23:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:5-Lev21:8\">LEV 21:5–21:8</a></p>\n<h3>The Nazirites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:8\">NUM 6:1–6:8</a></p>\n<h3>The apostles and prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:70\">LUK 1:70</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:21\">ACT 3:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:5\">EPH 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:2\">2PE 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Christians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Consecration sets apart for holiness</h2>\n<h3>God's people are consecrated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7-Lev20:8\">LEV 20:7–20:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10-Exod19:11\">EXO 19:10–19:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:14-Exod19:15\">EXO 19:14–19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:5\">JOS 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:13\">JOS 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:5\">1SA 16:5</a></p>\n<h3>Priests are consecrated for divine service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:30\">EXO 30:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:12-Exod40:15\">EXO 40:12–40:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:1\">1SA 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:14\">1CH 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:6\">2CH 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:5\">2CH 29:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:3\">2CH 35:3</a></p>\n<h3>Articles are consecrated for divine use</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9-Exod40:11\">EXO 40:9–40:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:36-Exod29:37\">EXO 29:36–29:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25-Exod30:29\">EXO 30:25–30:29</a></p>\n<h2>Days and occasions set apart for God</h2>\n<h3>The Sabbath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:1-Lev23:3\">LEV 23:1–23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:3\">GEN 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:23-Exod16:25\">EXO 16:23–16:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:11\">EXO 20:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Passover</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:4-Lev23:8\">LEV 23:4–23:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:16\">NUM 28:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:25\">NUM 28:25</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Weeks</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:16\">LEV 23:15–23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:21\">LEV 23:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:26\">NUM 28:26</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Trumpets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:23-Lev23:25\">LEV 23:23–23:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:1\">NUM 29:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:2\">NEH 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:9-Neh8:11\">NEH 8:9–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:28\">LEV 23:26–23:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:32\">LEV 23:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7\">NUM 29:7</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Tabernacles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:33-Lev23:36\">LEV 23:33–23:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a></p>\n<h3>The sabbath year</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:1-Lev25:5\">LEV 25:1–25:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Year of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:12\">LEV 25:8–25:12</a></p>\n<h2>Places identified with the presence of God are made holy</h2>\n<h3>Holy ground</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:5\">EXO 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:15\">JOS 5:15</a></p>\n<h3>Holy mountains</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:18-Exod19:23\">EXO 19:18–19:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:18\">2PE 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>The tabernacle</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:42-Exod29:44\">EXO 29:42–29:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9\">EXO 40:9</a></p>\n<h3>The temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:3\">1KI 9:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:16\">2CH 7:16</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:10-1Kgs8:13\">1KI 8:10–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:14\">EZK 42:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:20\">EZK 42:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:15\">MAT 24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:13\">ACT 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:28\">ACT 21:28</a></p>\n<h3>Jerusalem and the holy land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:17\">JOL 3:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:12\">ZEC 2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:5\">MAT 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:53\">MAT 27:53</a></p>\n<h2>Things associated with worship are holy</h2>\n<h3>Bread</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:32-Exod29:33\">EXO 29:32–29:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:3-1Sam21:6\">1SA 21:3–21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:3-Matt12:4\">MAT 12:3–12:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:25-Mark2:26\">MRK 2:25–2:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:3-Luke6:4\">LUK 6:3–6:4</a></p>\n<h3>Perfume</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34-Exod30:38\">EXO 30:34–30:38</a></p>\n<h3>Ritual offerings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:24-Lev6:29\">LEV 6:24–6:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:17\">LEV 6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:1\">LEV 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:6\">LEV 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:12-Lev10:13\">LEV 10:12–10:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:16-Lev10:18\">LEV 10:16–10:18</a></p>\n<h3>Offerings dedicated with a vow</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:9\">LEV 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:14\">LEV 27:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:20-Lev27:23\">LEV 27:20–27:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:28\">LEV 27:28</a></p>\n<h3>Tithes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30-Lev27:33\">LEV 27:30–27:33</a></p>\n<h3>The firstborn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:2\">EXO 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:11-Exod13:12\">EXO 13:11–13:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22-Luke2:23\">LUK 2:22–2:23</a></p>",
